{"questionId":"22581","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>In this question you will be exploring the strategies required to solve a system of linear differential equations.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Consider the system of linear differential equations of the form:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math>,</p>\n<p>where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;is a parameter.</p>\n<p>First consider the case where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>t</mi></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>t</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;into differential equation in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mtext>t</mtext></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>t</mi></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mtext>t</mtext></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>t</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22581","referenceCode":"21N.3.AHL.TZ0.2a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that dxdt-x=-Aet.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}